Sentencas: Protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFCs) show great potential in terms of lowering the operation temperature and overall cost of solid oxide fuel cells based on the high ionic conductivity and low activation energy of proton-conducing electrolytes in intermediate or low temperature environments.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode

Sentencas: However, a significant reduction in anode activity with decreasing temperature hinders the broad application of PCFCs.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode

Sentencas: In this study, a novel anode material Ni-Ba-0.96(Ce0.66Zr0.1Y0.2Ni0.04)O3-delta (Ni-BCZNY) with in-situ exsolved Ni nanoparticles is developed.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode

Sentencas: This material exhibits extremely high activity in PCFCs in intermediate and low temperatures.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode

Sentencas: A cell fabricated with this anode material achieves a power density of 912 mW cm(-2) and polarization resistance of 0.04 Omega cm(-2) in wet H-2/air at 700 degrees C. Additionally, the microstructure, electrochemical performance, electrochemical impedance, and electrode processes of a Ni-BCZNY cell are analyzed in detail.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode

Sentencas: The results indicate that performance enhancements can be attributed to the Ni nanoparticle exsolution promoting charge transfer and hydrogen dissociative adsorption.
Titulo: A high-performance intermediate-to-low temperature protonic ceramic fuel cell with in-situ exsolved nickel nanoparticles in the anode
